          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "TOF"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Photoneutron energy distributions froma target",
                "of liquefied natural neon were obtained by",
                "conventional time of flights methods. Measurements",
                "were made at an angle of 90 degrees to the photon",
                "beam for bremsstrahlung endpoint energies increasing",
                "in 1 MeV steps from 19 to 32 MeV. Photoneutron time",
                "of flight distributions were measured over the flight",
                "path of 32 m at a resolution of 0.4 ns/m,",
                "corresponding to a neutron resolution of 11 keV at 1",
                "MeV and 300 keV at 9 MeV."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "ANALYSIS": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CORAB"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " To deduce the 20Ne cross sections, a small",
                "contribution due to the 9% abundant 22Ne isotope has",
                "been subtracted from the natural neon spectra. This",
                "22Ne contribution was estimated from neutrons",
                "observed beyond the kinematic limit for 20Ne by",
                "assuming that these decayed through the ground state",
                "of 21Ne."
              ]
            }
          ],
